caption: Large portions and super friendly!
I love this place!
Pricey, but worth it as a treat once in awhile.

Now let me tell you, I'm an east-coaster with a ton of fresh seafood experience. I have explored.the fruits of the ocean from Florida to Maine but the Hawaiian Lobster Roll scene is at its top. Jolenes market aka Da Buttah Lobstah is one of my top contenders on the island for best Lobster roll!  First, the Lobster is incredible. It's served as a Lobster salad with big huge chunks of Lobster meat in every bite. It's got a nice refreshing Asian Slaw that compliments the Lobster so well, but the game changer here, yes... the game changer, is the split top roll. I dont know how they make it but it's like an elevated Hawaiian Roll - its sweet, but firm, but also light and fluffy. If you have a big mouth like me, you will struggle fitting this sandwich in, but once you get all those flavors swirling and mixing together, you won't put the sandwich down. And it's packed, no... overflowing with goodness, so.when your done, there's a good bit left on the plate, fortunately it's served with a fork. I got mine with fries. They were a pretty standard fry, no complaints and they were served crispy and hot! This is probably my 3rd or so review here and it's top quality and consistent everytime!

OMG! One of the BEST lobster rolls, easy online ordering, curbside pickup. Hot, fresh, accurate...yummy!! Love the combo special $1 extra for tomato bisque or corn chowder, $2  additional for assorted trees of fries. Good combo deal
Great food, friendly and pleasant staff.
Great atmosphere even better food! Get the prime rib roll or the lobster roll!

Brisket fried rice for my lunch. They know how to cook rice properly! It depends on how you like, but their fried rice is best in Honolulu. And it is with chunks of brisket. This is the champion of fried rice!
Food is sooo good
Our first time here but on our go to list for a while. My wife had the lobster roll and I had the brisket sandwich. Both were awesome. So much to try here.
Their food is delicious, but if you have a problem with dairy products; they have other choices to choose from.
The food was very good and great customer service.
Brisket melt! #need
Anytime somebody questions my favorite restaurant on the island, Jolene’s is always at or near the top. Everything my we’ve ever had there is unique and phenomenal. Highly recommend!

Went for lunch to try the infamous Lobster Roll. Got it with a side of sweet potato fries. While I was there, thought I'd try the Spicy Sausage Roll too with some chowder. Naturally,  they were busy, even with tourists on their way to the airport.  Good to see. Ordering takeout was reasonably quick and painless although, getting lucky with front door parking definitely helped. Service was pretty quick and was great to see staff helping each other. Personally,  I'd limit service to only takeout so they can turn parking faster, but that's just me. In all, worth the wait and definitely the best valued lobster roll in town so far at $18, (s/p fries +$2). It's a hearty and tasty sandwich.  Feast in Manoa is next on my list but Jolene's was worth trying, and I will definitely go back at some point to dabble in the rest of the menu. Simple but variety. The spicy sausage was also pretty good and came with a homemade slaw. I gotta say though, their buttered, toasted, house baked sweet roll is part of their secret. It kinda rocks and compliments both sandwiches. Anyway, pretty lengthy review on my part, on purpose.  Rock the Lobster Roll!  2/23/21 Just been to their last competitor in town. Jolene's rocks the best Lobstah Roll in town, especially for the price. Nice job guys!

Food is good & cashiers are great.  Although I did eat in once & the experience was ok.  Had to ask to get water twice becuase after the waitor served us our food he never came back.  When my wife went up to the counter he was talking story in the kitchen so the cashier brought us our water the 2 times my wife went & asked for it.  After the 2nd time my wife asked for water, the cashier took it upon herself to check on us.

If you love Spicy food ... I dare you to get the spicy KNFC (korean nashville fried chicken) we had to get a side of the amazing hot sauce. The fried chicken and gravy was amazing as well with a side of pickled vegetables.
Great food,  big portions

Its so nice inside. I ordered the lobster roll. OMG, it was outstanding! The best lobster roll I have ever had. The seafood was so fresh, the garlic bun was made with perfection, and the pickled veggies was out of this world.

Heard of this place by word of mouth from Ms. Zena. Myself, Ms. Roberta and my son Mr. Keoki ate here 08 Feb 21 WOW Factor Major Ono Grinds and the slushies to Die For. Reasonably Priced Plenty Of Food. GOTS TO CHECK THIS PLACE OUT.
Delicious lobster roll with generous serving of lobster. Friendly staff, great service!

We really enjoyed the unique and delicious lobster rolls. The split sweet rolls, so fresh and soft, were grilled just right to contain the massive amount of deliciously seasoned lobster filling.  Come hungry and be satisfied!
Oh wow... You must try the lobster roll!!! Dealing with parking can be a hassle but worth it. I'll be going back.
The food is amazing. Limited seating now because of covid which is expected. Excellent service.
Lobster roll...price has crept up, but it is still the bomb! ☺️

Oh my Yumminess! I ate here one day for lunch since it is near my office and then I took my kids the next week because I knew it would be a good treat and they would love it. They totally did! They were so happy with their food and sitting down to eat that they even stopped with me to take a selfie (WITH THEIR MOM!!!!) in front of the 'Garden Wall'. That's a win and totally worth it. Food was phenomenal. We had the Birria Melt, fried chicken sandwich and the lobster roll. As well as a strawberry li heng lemonade. Everything was really good. They will put an 18% tip onto your bill - Just FYI. Okay by me, just makes it easier.

Unbelievable lobster rolls. Generous portion of lobster for the price. The pickled daikon in there really adds a deliciously unique twist to an already tasty bite. Chicken sandwich was super delicious as well. I especially like that they use dark meat and the coleslaw matches the sauce perfectly.

Fast friendly service. I ordered through the website. The slushee flavors they had sounded amazing. Very cute interior. Indoor seating available during Covid. Hand sanitizer available. Employees wearing masks. Parking is a little tight and lot is right off Main Street.

Jolene is located to the left behind the plaza center stage. The staff is extremely friendly. Couldn't decide between the lobster butter roll or the lobster benny roll so we got both!  All the food was delicious. They don't take reservations and there isn't much tables so best to get there early before the crowds.
Parking was good.  Food was good. Took 20+ min to get the food..at least we know its made fresh. You might luck out and get curly and regular fries with you waffle fries.
Delicious
Their Milk Tea and Spicy chicken sandwich is to die for! Popeyes doesn't come close to how delicious Jolene's is!!
The lobster rolls 😋😋😋
I haven't been here to the location itself. But have ordered through UberEats! I love the brisket plate. It makes a pregnant lady so happy!!
One of my fav fried chicken sandwiches 🤤 you must try! It's huge. Great jaw exercise 😂🍔🙌🏼

I’m leaving a 1 star review purely for the fact that when they rang up the charge they put a mandatory 15% gratuity. I’m all for tipping and if service is awesome I’ll tip upwards of 30%. But to be charged basically a fee for someone that may or may not serve me properly isn’t right. Sorry not sorry left went elsewhere. Too bad their food looks great I just refuse to be made to do something that is purely subjective.

Parking wasn't great, but thats downtown for you.  What was amazing was the Birria Melt. Holy smokes, the meat was tender and the cheese was perfect. In between the thick cut bread I didn't feel like I had to rush to keep the sandwich in tact. The dipping sauce it came with was jam packed with flavor, not very spicy, but filled with an incredible aromatic experience. I definitely reccomended getting a melt if you're around.
This place is a gem!! Both the tuna melt and lobster melt were delicious!! Slushy was great!! Will definitely order again!
Awesome. Couldn't have been better...
Came for the lobster roll and was not disappointed. Location and parking is your only challenge.

Absolutely amazing!  Atmosphere is great, they did a stellar job on the interior design. The food we ordered was super flavorful and cooked to perfection.  We had the lobster melt and chicken sandwich. And I must say the chicken sandwich reminds me of chic fil-a, but better!

Wow, this place is great! A new favorite for sure. They have an amazing staff, which was very helpful, accommodating, a pleasure to deal with. As if that wasn’t enough, the atmosphere is clean and nice. The food (and slushees) are just flavorful and filling! For the quality and amount of food you get, unquestionably worth it. Both of our melts had a good portion of protein spread to every corner. They didn’t go light on the melts at all! Again, you can’t not go wrong with trying this place out! Well worth it and will be going back to get more in the future! Honestly can’t think of anything else they can do to make this place better.
I am rating food quality, because of Covid19, I'll give them a pass on service and attitude;)
Great spot for creations you won’t see many other places!
Pork grind old. Food is a bit over priced
The lobster melt is awesome. The lobster roll is okay but nothing like the melt. Sorry no pic but def get you a melt.
Tried this place for lunch based on a friends recommendation and it did not disappoint!! It was so delicious and fresh well worth the prices !!
Amazing food at reasonable prices. Their tuna melt is amazing!

Had the butta lobster roll. Disappointed because it seemed like a mixture of minced crab and lobster, didn’t seem very fresh either.  Taste was okay. $16 is not bad for a lobster roll as usually they are $20+ but would not order again.  Also had mushroom spinach melt, bread was good and crunchy.

this place has not disappointed me yet.  since my first visit I've done nothing but entice more people to try their menu. the lobster buttah roll has been my go to buy the 18 hour slow cooked beef brisket melt with birra consume, lobster waffle fries, birra noodle soup, and the biscoff cookie butter shake are great choices in my opinion as well.
Yummy place

My colleagues were raving about the Lobster roll so of course I had to try it. In my opinion it was just ok. Not bad, not amazing, just ok. Subpar. I also ordered the corn chowder and regular grilled cheese. I enjoyed the grilled cheese more then the lobster roll. The corn chowder was bland. I had high hopes for this place but was truly underwhelmed.
I love their sandwiches, especially the lobster melt.  Anything with lobster is great !
Loved it Great Customer Service

Wow, I'm stuffed! I can't believe how delicious dinner was. I ordered the Birria Cheese Melt and she got the Lobster Roll. Amazing! A side oder of sweet potato fries was a nice addition too. She enjoyed a Cookie Butter Milk, and let me tell you, it was so good. Similar to drinking an airline cookie milkshake, if there was such a thing. Everything was perfect. We dined in, so we were able to enjoy the interior design for a bit. I highly recommend eating here. I will most definitely be coming back to try their other menu items soon.

We had the Lobster Butter Roll, Lobster fries, and the Lobster melt and everything was amazing. My favorite was the melt but my wife enjoyed the roll. We've heard other things on their menu are tasty as well but this is what we had and it was great.
Tasty drinks and dinner interesting things for food on the menu. Will come back someday to try
Bomb food
Best sandwiches on island I've tried. I recommend the brisket melt. If you have kids, you can't go wrong with the grilled cheese.
Very reasonable prices with a great menu selection! Must try if you are in the area especially if are wanting a lobster roll. Not all lobster... Think there is also crab acting as a filler.

Very delicious food at moderate prices. I've tried the lobster roll, Korean Fried Chicken Sandwich, and BBQ Brisket melt. The lobster roll was very good. The roll was buttery and soft while the lobster was generous and tasty. The chicken sandwich, which I also got spicy, was not very impressive. Probably won't get that again. But the BBQ Brisket Melt is super yummy. Their brisket is slowly cooked, and you can taste all their spices and the smokiness but its also not too salty. Its wonderful! My favorite, I think. Prices are on average above $10 but their portions are pretty good and I think, well worth it. See what all the hype is about for yourself! (Also, there is parking right in front of the store front off of S.Beretania St. The spaces are limited, maybe about 10. But there's also street parking and parking in the plaza, as well.)
The food and service were great!!! The lobster roll and prime rib sandwhich were, to die for!!😋
Soo good! One of those places that's really hard to decide what to order.

I love their Lobster butter roll. When I got it first time, I thought it was overpriced, but after I ate it, realized that it's worth it. That it very big portion of shredded lobster and buns are so yum, and pay $ 1 comes with tomato bisque soup I chose. Inside shop is very spacey and comfy. Must try if you live in Hawaii.

We waited in line for about 25 mins before we got to order.  We ordered Lobster roll sandwich- not my favorite like someone mentioned it tasted like caned Lobster meat the bread/ fries was cold the whole plate was okay, we also had spicy sausage dog -hubby said it was good m,  fried chicken sandwich to much breading on the chicken, it was falling all over the place, we also had brisket that was good.  We ordered a Strawberry/Mango smoothie I think it was best out of everything.  Oh CHECK your order before you leave.
Went to try their brisket melt... was so good! Ordered ube jin dui, but it was burnt and only a touch of ube.
Delicious!!
After a 20 minute wait and $2 apiece for ube jin dui, it was disappointingly small, filled with very little filling, and smelled overcooked/burnt. Little dissappointing =(
Awesome loco moco!!!

I patiently waited 42 minutes for my take out order just to be disappointed when I got home & my order was not complete. I called & they apologized but did nothing to rectify the problem. Food was good, but disappointed that I didn't get all of my order.
Ordered the lobster roll, the bun was incredible but I couldn't tell if it was canned crab or lobster was minced and shredded. Over priced. Lobster rolls need to have big chunks of lobster!!
Lunch ,fair priced
Wonderful food and fantastic service! Definitely plan to order from here again soon!

Parking right out front, order at the counter then choose your table. They bring the food & drinks to you. We had the....Bbq brisket fries - tender bbq brisket, melted shredded cheese, green onions drizzle of bbq sauce on a bed of crisp waffle fries. Grilled cheese made with Japanese white bread and a SERIOUSLY awesome cheese pull. The Buttah burger Classic - grilled Brioche bun, thick & well seasoned patty,  Cheese pull (so unexpected!!), and the usual fixings that come on a deluxe burger minus the onions. Great drink menu that includes smoothies, lemonade, and pearl teas. I've yet to try everything. But they're so awesome I'll definitely be back for more!
Can you say lobster roll and corn chowder! YES!!
Lobster Roll and Corn Chowder for the win!
Great service. The fried chicken sandwich was awesome

This is where you will find the butter lobster roll! If you are from the East Coast it may not be as good but for Hawaii it is really close. As the saying goes, "when in Rome". I will not be picky but at least it fulfills my lobster roll craving. Enjoy!
First timer, had the Lobster Roll!!! YUMMMM!!!! Buttery Texas Toasted Bread lettuce and chunks and shreds of Lobsters. If you love seafood, it's a must try! Will be back to taste other dishes.
Best Lobster Roll in the world!!! And the Hamburger steak plate is huge and TASTY!!
(Translated by Google) Located in the cultural center of Chinatown. A set of lobster roll and chowder is recommended!  (Original) チャイナタウンのカルチャラルセンターにあります。ロブスターロールとチャウダーのセットがお薦めです！
The best Lobster roll ever!!!!
It was ok, not my favorite places to dine at.
Had lobster roll and chowder combination, it was very good!

My friend and I had lobster roll with chowder.  The food itself was alright.  However the service was not so nice.  My food came out almost right away which was great.  Then waited for at least 10-15 minutes for my friend, nothing to be found.  When he went up and asked, the lady just said "Later".   What kind of response is that?  then we continued to wait for another 5-10 minutes till food come out.   The food could have been better if I didn't wait for my friend's food to come out.
Good happy hour deals and great food. Grilled cheese and lobster was my favorite. The lobster roll could have used more bread, it was more like an open faced sandwich
Very nice,  good food. Lots of tanks to east at even large groups
Good food and price
Great lobster roll and lobster grilled cheese, lost of lobster
Excellent lobster rolls! Excellent lobster grilled cheese! Well worth the stop great food!
Lobster roll is the bomb.
Fast service. Clean. Must try lobster roll. You can also ha e Dave's ice cream in the same area. Plenty of seating. Love the koi decor.
Lobster roll was delicious! Kids loved the noodles!

Lobster roll was mushy and did not taste like fresh lobster.  The bread was the best part of the dish.  Their clam chowder was homemade but I had a marble sized chunk of flour in mine.  The wife's lobster grilled cheese was greasy and flavorless
Lobster roll is meh
Tasteful food but lil pricey for my taste. Small parking lot in front.

This is a great multi-kiosk location, while it was designed with the concept of having the ability to change a kiosk from one service to another, it looks like their current choices are really good.  1) Seafood 2) Hongkong style Chinese food 3) Deserts 4) Bar  The staff is always friendly and while sometimes they get really busy (can't serve everyone fast when it's to busy), most of the time you get great service, good food, and of course there's a bar!!!
Lobster roll was decent. Not special enough at the price point they offer to return.

I thought this was a reataurant (like Regal Bakery before it) but actually this is a miniature food court. It's a large space with sit down tables but no booths. Along one wall is a kitchen and prep area with menus on blackboards, near the door is a bar area and a drink counter that offers coffee, tea, boba tea, and smoothies.  Ambience is noisy, you can hear the coversation at the next table. A TV behind the bar is playing '80s music videos, notably a-ha's Take On Me and Queen's Bohemian Rhapsody.
Very nice place tucked inside the chinese cultural center. The decor is nice and the wait is friendly.

Best traditional Chinese-style seafood, best place to eat it at in Chinatown, hands down. Bistro bar atmosphere on one side, high-end fish market on other side. Friendly and attentive service, fresh top-quality ingredients cooked well and served as if homestyle comfort food at your Auntie's kitchen table. This place was packed on a Wed for lunch hour(for good reason😉), be prepared to wait. Ordering is a little confusing. Extensive food and drink menu, not just seafood. Lobster and braised beef were perfection.

Nice clean restaurant. Lobster roll was very tasty.  Spicy sausage roll was very good and not over powering in the spiciness. The Sally and vinegar chance wings could use more salt and vinegar. Noodles was crispy with tender beef.

I love Jolene's Market ! The variety of Chinese food is wonderful ! There are a lot of items on the menu that other places don't offer. My favorite is the chicken feet soup ( hangover cure ) It actually states that on the menu, although I don't drink. They also have a bar area. They also serve the lobster roll and there's even ice cream !
Awesome lobster rolls! And lobster grilled cheese too!

Wanted this place to do well with re vamp from Regal bakery.  Gf ordered pork fried rice and was in edible.  She didn't have the gumption to tell them food was over salted and rice had hard plastic like texture.  My other bff Paul had a heavy disappointment with the lobster rolls.  He brought a bunch of co workers with him and was embarrassed by the lack of quality control.  First time he tried the lobster he was delighted at the quantity of 2 claws in his roll.  Second time around it was significantly smaller with only 1 claw.  After raving about it to all his friends and family only to find it sub par.  Paul talked to Charlene about it and was told they have no control over the quality of their foods.  She was extremely rude summing it up that he didn't need to come through her doors if he doesn't like it. Would highly recommend you take your business elsewhere.  I work too hard for my money to be spent at such an undeserving establishment.

Brand New best of Asian diner bar and grill. Premium Liquor and great international cuisine. The lobster pricing is an exceptional value. Happy hour specials from 4-7 PM HST daily. I really like this place!

We came for lunch for lobster rolls and grilled cheese, then did drinks for more lobster plus bar foods. For the price, you get a lot of lobster. The bulk is a lobster salad type filling but generous chunks throughout in both sandwiches. Most places here do lobster rolls like it's tuna salad but the dressing on these is light and not to mayo-y. Also like the pairing with bahn mi style veggies in the roll. Bar is limited but good prices and generous pours if you want basic drinks. It got super crowded around 6pm on Friday so might need a reservation if you have a big group. They also do Chinese food (which looked great and we're going back to try, coffees and Dave's ice cream ... Like 20 flavors). I like the variety. Parking at Cultural Plaza. It's in the old Regal Bakery space.

I had the lobster roll, which really wasn't a roll just the Lobster mix on toast. In any case, the flavor was delicious with nice big chunks of lobster. Bread got soggy and it was a messy experience, but overall good. The corn chowder was not too special. I went at 12:30  and the place was busy and noisy. The young lady who took my order was smiley and friendly, the lady who served me didn't look at me, just set the food down and walked away.
Great food and yummy food, really recommend for family time!

Jolene's Market is a clean, AC food court with your meal, dessert, & drinks all in one place! Lobster grilled cheese was amazing! 😍 Dunno what they do to that bread, but the whole thing is melt in your mouth delicious! Homemade tomato bisque is not smooth, but flavor is on point! Momo's fruit smoothies are very flavorful! They also have yummy desserts, ice cream, & milk teas!

Went here for dinner last night. The restaurant was crowded but not overwhelming. After 25 minutes I recieved a quarter of my meal. Waiting another 30 minutes still not receiving the rest, upon asking, they told me it would be another 20-30 minutes. I watched dozens of people order after me, eat, and leave before even getting my food. Mistakes happen, but the fact that they lied and said it was still cooking (chicken fried rice no less) instead of being honest about a mistake, was unsettling. Then argued with for a refund for the food I did not receive. I will not be returning.
Good food good location good service

Jolene's Market is a family owned business with a great feel. I had the loster roll and chowder and the lobster roll was truly the star! Coming from the east coast this lobster roll really ranks high.
Loved their Lobster Roll that came with a small cup of creamy soup. Satisfied my craving!!
Great food and really good service.
